ITV.Tour.de.France.2014.Stage.6.Highlights.PDTV.x264-NX

Thursday 10th July 2014 ITV4
7pm to 8pm Highlights

Highlights of stage six which continues its commemoration of the 100th anniversary of the start of WW1 with today's route passing through the sites of the Battle of the Somme and the Chemin des Dames. 194km long with many twists and turns in the finale, stage six might just see a breakaway hold off the charging peloton and cheat the sprinters out of a victory. Presented by Gary Imlach with analysis from Chris Boardman, commentary by Phil Liggett and Paul Sherwen with Ned Boulting and Matt Rendell the reporters at the roadside.
